  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Assistance to Vulnerable Internally Displaced Persons, Returnees and Host Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is part of the emergency humanitarian response conducted in Mali with the overall objective of providing humanitarian assistance to conflict-affected populations in the center and north of the country. In order to alleviate the suffering of the populations, IOM offers assistance, which is structured around three axes, namely the protection aspect through the monitoring of the movement of populations through the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM) which will support the Government of Mali in the collection of data. The second aspect of IOM&apos;s assistance is to improve access to shelter/non-food items to vulnerable populations in areas with a high concentration of internally displaced persons and returnees. The third axis will assure a protection response for affected and displaced households and host communities through psychosocial assistance and will respond to the proven need for clinical care for people with mental health problems.</narrative>
  </description>
